{%- comment -%}
  "Pairs well with" upsell strip (spec §7: "2 mini cards, one-tap add").
  Rendered inline inside cart-drawer.liquid rather than fetched separately —
  the whole drawer already re-renders via the cart AJAX API's `sections`
  param after every change (see assets/cart-utils.js), so a second,
  independent async fetch just for this strip would be redundant.

  Uses Shopify's native recommendation engine (intent: 'complementary',
  distinct from the PDP's 'related' — see sections/related-products.liquid)
  based on the cart's first item, and reuses product-form-button.liquid's
  existing <quick-add-button> wiring verbatim for "one-tap add" — that
  element already does a real /cart/add.js call and dispatches `cart:updated`
  (built in Milestone 4), so this needs zero new add-to-cart logic.

  "Mini cards" intentionally don't reuse the full product-card.liquid (badges,
  hover states, wishlist/compare actions) — too heavy for a compact strip;
  composes responsive-image/price/product-form-button directly instead, same
  approach as Milestone 7's complete-the-look.liquid.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- if settings.cart_show_upsell and cart.item_count > 0 -%}
  {% recommendations product: cart.items.first.product, limit: 2, intent: 'complementary' %}
    {%- if recommendations.performed and recommendations.products_count > 0 -%}
      <div class="cart-upsell">
        <p class="kicker">{{ 'cart.upsell_heading' | t }}</p>
        <div class="cart-upsell__items">
          {%- for recommended_product in recommendations.products -%}
            <div class="cart-upsell__item">
              <a href="{{ recommended_product.url }}" class="cart-upsell__media aspect-ratio" style="aspect-ratio: 1/1;" tabindex="-1" aria-hidden="true">
                {% render 'responsive-image', image: recommended_product.featured_image, sizes: '64px', wrap: false %}
              </a>
              <div class="cart-upsell__info">
                <a href="{{ recommended_product.url }}" class="cart-upsell__title">{{ recommended_product.title }}</a>
                {% render 'price', product: recommended_product, size: 'card' %}
              </div>
              {% render 'product-form-button', product: recommended_product %}
            </div>
          {%- endfor -%}
        </div>
      </div>
    {%- endif -%}
  {% endrecommendations %}
{%- endif -%}
